Notes: An attractive small tree, especially suited to coastal S-E QLD areas on sand. New leaves are red to reddish-brown

Butterfly Type: Small butterflies called Line-blues lay their eggs on it, and the larvae eat some of the flowers and flower buds. Also a number of other small butterflies lay their eggs on it, such as Fiery Jewel, Blue Jewel, Wattle Blue and Glistening Blue. Their larvae eat juvenile leaves and flower buds.
Notes: A common tree of S-E QLD that is found over a wide variety of soils.

Butterfly Type: Small butterflies called Line-blues lay eggs on the plant and the larvae feed on the flowers and flower buds.
Notes: Large attractive rainforest tree with dense foliage. New foliage reddish and pendulous

Butterfly Type: Small butterflies called Line-blues lay their eggs on it, and the larvae eat some of the flowers and flower buds.
Notes: A small open shrub with prickly foliage but attractive puff-ball flowers in spring.

Butterfly Type: Small butterflies called Line-blues lay their eggs on it, and the larvae eat some of the flowers and flower buds. Also a few other butterfly species such as the large pretty Tailed Emperor lay their eggs on it, and the larvae eat the leaves.
Notes: An attractive large shrub with pretty foliage and  massed flowers in autumn and spring.

Butterfly Type: Small butterflies called Line-blues lay their eggs on it, and the larvae eat some of the flowers and flower buds.
Notes: An open shrub with prickly foliage but delightful small cream puff-ball flowers in winter to spring.

Butterfly Type: Small butterflies called Line-blues lay their eggs on it, and the larvae eat some of the flowers and flower buds. The large pretty Tailed Emperor and the Large Grass-yellow also lay their eggs on it, and the larvae eat the foliage.
Notes: A hardy wattle that is handy as an understorey plant.

Butterfly Type: Small butterflies called Line-blues lay their eggs on it, and the larvae eat some of the flowers and flower buds.
Notes: An attractive shrub with massed yellow puff-ball wattle flowers in winter to spring.

Butterfly Type: Small butterflies called Line-blues lay their eggs on it and the larvae eat some of the flowers and flower buds.
Notes: An attractive shrub with subtle white rod-shaped wattle flowers in summer to autumn.

Butterfly Type: Small butterflies called Line-blues lay their eggs on it, and the larvae eat some of the flowers and flower buds. Also the large pretty Tailed Emperor and the Large Grass-yellow lay their eggs on it and the larvae eat the leaves.
Notes: A common hardy long-lived wattle.

Butterfly Type: Small butterflies called Line-blues lay their eggs on it, and the larvae eat some of the flowers and flower buds. A number of other small butterflies lay their eggs on it and the larvae eat the foliage.
Notes: An attractive shrub with pretty feathery foliage and heavy displays of wattle flowers throughout the year.
An attractive small rainforest tree that is quite dense, and hardy.
An attractive dense small tree that is hardy.
A narrow tree that has beautiful stiff palm-like leaves. Protection from drying out and harsh sun and wind.
An attractive hardy small tree with small pendulous clusters of white flowers.
A very attractive plant with its holly-like foliage which provides some protection to nesting birds. New foliage is red or reddish brown.
A very attractive plant with large foliage and bunches of perfumed bell-shaped flowers.
A vigorous vine for a native garden, climbing on fences and up trees. Clusters of dense cream flowers in spring.
An attractive small dense tree with flushes of bright red new growth.
An attractive rainforest tree with reddish new growth.
A very hardy dense growing shrub especially in full sun. Attractive to honey-eaters and lorikeets (flowers). Fairly tolerant of poorly drained soils.
Small open shrub for pot culture, or in well-drained soils. Pretty pink star-shaped flowers in spring.
An attractive rainforest plant for shady locations (or partial shade) with flushes of red new leaf growth.

A rare large impressive tree that develops a characteristic swollen trunk. Can be semi-deciduous in flowering season. Seeds would be edible like other Brachychiton species. Flowers are small of a greenish cream colour.

Butterfly Type: The Eastern Flat butterfly lays its eggs on the leaves and the caterpillars eat some of the leaves.
Notes: Has serrated shiny leaves with contrasting pale fuzzy undersides and the new growth is bronze coloured with rusty hairs. It flowers in late spring to early summer with lemon coloured fluffy flowers which resemble Acacia flowers and.
A narrow rare tree that develops a slightly broader pencil-pine type shape.

An attractive shrub or small tree that responds to pruning and produces small ball-shaped white flowers from late winter to spring. Useful as a hedging plant although it doesn't stay very dense usually.

An interesting rare native rainforest tree that stays relatively dense in foliage and produces masses of small fluffy creamy-white flowers from late winter to spring. Larger trees develop an impressive buttressed trunk. The bark is smooth and dappled in greens, browns and greys.
A small hardy dense rainforest tree with clusters of tiny white flowers.
A very rare native shrub with masses of small yellow flowers throughout the year.
An attractive native palm-like plant for a shady moist position. The foliage gives a tropical look.
A very attractive native plan that produces massed displays of tiny white flowers.
A native hardy rainforest shrub for a shady site. It produces attractive red 15mm fruit.

Butterfly Type: A few species of tiny butterflies called Line-blues lay their eggs on the flower buds and the caterpillars eat some of these buds.
Notes: An attractive small narrow rare rainforest plant
A very hardy native small tree that can tolerate some salty wind and exposure along the coast. Has small red to orange fruit
An attractive small native plant ideally suited to a pot or in the ground in well-drained soil.
An attractive small native plant for a pot or in well-drained soil if planted in the ground
A very attractive small tree with its weeping wattle-like foliage and masses of small golden pea flowers.
Has black fruitAn attractive hardy small rainforest tree that has massed weeping foliage, often with pinkish-brown new growth. In appearance it is similar to a small Lillipilli tree.
An attractive hardy small tree with glossy foliage and clusters of small white flowers. Small orange fruit splits to display seeds, attracting birds.
An attractive small rainforest tree with decorative foliage. Has small black fruit
A very attractive and very hardy small native tree with very attractive dense foliage. New growth is often red. Has small red fruit
A dense tall rainforest tree with small red fruit
An attractive native rainforest tree to create a shade area. New growth is often pink or red.
A hardy small native rainforest tree with masses of attractive bird-attracting small orange fruit.
An attractive tall narrow rainforest tree for a large area. Produces masses of tiny yellow flowers followed by oblong seed capsules splitting into 5 segments.
A leafy climbing plant that grows well on fences. The soft green new shoot is edible as a raw vegetable.
A small rainforest tree with attractive dense foliage, attractive smooth dappled bark, and masses of small white flowers which attract bees. The small black fruit are edible.
A hardy narrow rainforest tree with wattle-like foliage and delicate small grevillea flowers.

Butterfly Type: The large Tailed Emperor butterfly lays its eggs on the plant and the caterpillars eat some of the leaves.
Notes: A very attractive small rainforest plant that needs regular watering and protection when getting established, but then is quite hardy. The yellow flowers in summer are quite attractive.  Has small black fruit
A very attractive groundcover for a well-drained sunny position. The 25mm yellow flowers occur throughout the year.
A hardy small rainforest tree with small delicate flowers.  Has small red fruit
An attractive small annual plant with purple flowers for a sunny well-drained position. It is poisonous though.
An attractive vine for fences. It can be quite vigorous in its growth so benefits from pruning occasionally. Perfumed Jasmine flowers in autumn to spring. Has small black fruit
An attractive scrambling vine useful on fences. Perfumed white Jasmine flowers from autumn to spring. Has small black fruit
A delicate but hardy climber that sometimes will just scramble at ground level. Perfumed Jasmine flowers from spring to summer and small black fruit.
A small tree or large shrub with dense foliage for a preferably reasonably sunny well-drained position. Very similar to a Leptospermum in appearance.
A very hardy tall shrub with dense foliage and massed white flowers in spring.
An attractive large shrub with massed small white flowers in summer. Sheds its bark each year.
An attractive large shrub with massed small white flowers in summer. Leaves are strongly lemon-scented.
An attractive narrow upright shrub that flowers best in a sunny spot.  Attractive fern-like foliage.
Attractive vine with ferny foliage. Produces suckers from the base.
Hardy small rainforest tree or tall shrub. Produces a distinctive 'rainforest' odour.
Small attractive hardy rainforest plant, can tolerate shady locations.
Small dense rainforest tree which performs well in cultivation. Very hardy. Lightly-perfumed flowers are produced throughout the year, with massed flowering in spring and summer.
Attractive dense small tree that is relatively tolerant of poor drainage. White papery bark and bottlebrush type flowers.
Attractive small tree or tall shrub with weeping branches. Regarded as a rare species. Small bottlebrush flowers attract honey-eaters and dense foliage provides nesting sites.
Relatively dense shrub with masses of creamy white bottlebrush flowers. Prickly foliage provides good nesting sites for smaller birds.
Attractive small tree with dense foliage which is red when yound, and creamy-white bottlebrush flowers.
Attractive small shrub, does best in a sunny site
Attractive small rainforest tree. Small red fruit open to reveal purple flesh.
Attractive hardy rainforest tree, glossy foliage gives a tropical look
